  }))), "core things"), mdx("p", null, "I was about twenty years old, and I started writing for the school's independent magazine, which allowed me to write about almost anything, as long as it was related to school or university students. I liked the fact that I had a steady audience, and that's when I started to love paper publications."), mdx("p", null, "I practiced how to clarify what I wanted to say in my writing. Originally, I came in with the intention of writing a lot of makgeolli reviews or something like that, but in reality, I wrote a lot of articles about who did what to whom and it's really bad, and it's ruining the university society, and it's ruining the country."), mdx("p", null, "Naturally, I was trained to put core things in my writing. There was a time when I seriously tried to prepare to be a journalist. I gave up because it seemed like too much of a hated profession."), mdx("h2", {
